      "span_text": "TOM complex on the outer membrane of mitochondria was the entry gate for the proteins that were imported into the mitochondria  and was also found to be necessary for tBid/Bax-induced cytochrome C release.   Especially, among the members of TOM complex, TOM22 had been accepted as a mitochondrial receptor for Bax  and the cytosolic domain of TOM22 could modulate the mitochondrial translocation and conformation of Bax."
